# UIDesignState — The AI Design Contract

## What Is This?

`UIDesignState` (defined in `src/types/design-state.ts`) is the **read-only AI design contract** that constrains every structural and visual decision when creating a new page. It is not a runtime type — it is a specification language used during code generation.

> **CRITICAL**: AI MUST NOT extend the `archetype` enum or add new `intent` values. Any change to this interface requires explicit architect approval. The file header states: *"AI 不得自行扩展 archetype 或新增 intent."*

```typescript
// src/types/design-state.ts — READ-ONLY
export interface UIDesignState {
  intent:     'dashboard' | 'data-management' | 'form-workflow' | 'detail-view' | 'settings'
  context?:   'desktop-first' | 'mobile-first'
  archetype:  'A1-toolbar-content' | 'A2-sidebar-inspector' | 'A3-stats-grid' | 'A4-table-drawer' | 'A5-form-wizard'
  density:    'compact' | 'comfortable' | 'spacious'
  hierarchy:  'data-first' | 'action-first' | 'reading-first'
  emphasis:   'low' | 'medium' | 'high'
  ctaPolicy:  'minimal' | 'single-primary' | 'dual-primary'
}
```

---

## Dimension 1 — `intent` (Page Business Purpose)

| Value | Description | Default archetype |
|---|---|---|
| `'dashboard'` | KPI stats, real-time monitoring, metric overviews | `A3-stats-grid` |
| `'data-management'` | CRUD tables, sortable/filterable list views | `A4-table-drawer` |
| `'form-workflow'` | Multi-step forms, wizard flows, data entry | `A5-form-wizard` |
| `'detail-view'` | Read-heavy profile, inspection, or document pages | `A2-sidebar-inspector` |
| `'settings'` | Configuration panels, preferences, system setup | `A1-toolbar-content` |

---

## Dimension 2 — `context` (Responsive Bias, optional)

| Value | Implication |
|---|---|
| `'desktop-first'` | Optimize layout for ≥ 1280px; mobile is graceful degradation |
| `'mobile-first'` | Start from 375px viewport; progressive enhancement upward |
| _(omitted)_ | Inherit from global layout default (`desktop-first` for admin) |

---

## Dimension 3 — `archetype` (Layout Blueprint)

Pick the archetype matching the page's primary task. Do NOT mix archetypes on a single page.

| Archetype | Macro structure | Primary use case |
|---|---|---|
| `A1-toolbar-content` | Toolbar strip at top, scrollable content below | Settings, simple dashboards |
| `A2-sidebar-inspector` | Master list on the left, detail panel on the right | Profile detail, content inspection |
| `A3-stats-grid` | Stats row at top, chart/widget grid below | KPI dashboards, monitoring boards |
| `A4-table-drawer` | Full-width table, detail Drawer opens on row click | Data management, CRUD lists |
| `A5-form-wizard` | Stepper header + contained form area | Multi-step forms, onboarding wizards |

**[EXAMPLE] SKELETON OVERRIDE NOTICE:**
The `overflow-auto` classes in the examples below are illustrative ONLY. Per L2 Architecture Laws, production business views MUST replace scroll containers with `<CScrollbar class="col-fill">`.

**UnoCSS skeleton for each archetype:**

```html
<!-- A1: toolbar + scrollable content -->
<div class="col-fill">
  <div class="row-between p-sm bg-card border-b-default"><!-- toolbar / actions --></div>
  <div class="col-fill overflow-auto p-md gap-md"><!-- main content --></div>
</div>

<!-- A2: master-detail split -->
<div class="row-start col-fill">
  <div class="col-fill w-72 border-r-default overflow-auto p-sm"><!-- master list --></div>
  <div class="col-fill overflow-auto p-md"><!-- inspector / detail panel --></div>
</div>

<!-- A3: stats row + chart grid -->
<div class="col-fill gap-md p-md overflow-auto">
  <div class="row-start gap-md flex-wrap"><!-- stat cards --></div>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-md col-fill"><!-- chart widgets --></div>
</div>

<!-- A4: toolbar + table (Drawer managed by PrimeVue Drawer component) -->
<div class="col-fill">
  <div class="row-between p-sm bg-card border-b-default"><!-- search / filters / CTA --></div>
  <div class="col-fill overflow-hidden"><!-- <ProTable> fills remaining height --></div>
</div>

<!-- A5: stepper + form -->
<div class="col-center col-fill p-md overflow-auto">
  <div class="row-start gap-sm mb-md w-full max-w-3xl"><!-- step indicators --></div>
  <div class="bg-card rounded-md p-lg col-fill w-full max-w-3xl"><!-- <ProForm> --></div>
</div>
```

