## Dimension 4 — `density` (Page-Level Spacing Intent)

> **CRITICAL DISTINCTION**: `density` is a **page-level design decision** about information density. It is NOT the user's global `SizeMode` (`compact/comfortable/loose`). These are two independent systems. **NEVER** map `density` values to `useSizeStore().setSize()`.

| Value | Meaning | Recommended spacing token tier |
|---|---|---|
| `'compact'` | Dense information; maximize data rows per viewport | `p-xs` / `p-sm` / `gap-xs` / `gap-sm` |
| `'comfortable'` | Balanced layout (default for most admin pages) | `p-sm` / `p-md` / `gap-sm` / `gap-md` |
| `'spacious'` | Generous whitespace; reading or marketing focus | `p-md` / `p-lg` / `gap-md` / `gap-lg` |

`'spacious'` uses the `p-md`/`p-lg` token tier — **NOT** `useSizeStore().setSize('loose')`.

---

## Dimension 5 — `hierarchy` (Visual Priority)

| Value | Structural implication |
|---|---|
| `'data-first'` | Tables and data visualizations are primary; CTAs/actions are toolbar-bound |
| `'action-first'` | Primary CTA is visually dominant; data rows support the action decision |
| `'reading-first'` | Typography legibility and content flow take precedence; wide margins |

---

## Dimension 6 — `emphasis` (Visual Weight)

| Value | Shadow / Color guidance |
|---|---|
| `'low'` | `shadow-none` or omit; muted palette (`bg-muted`, `text-muted-foreground`); minimal contrast |
| `'medium'` | `shadow-sm`; standard semantic tokens (`bg-card`, `text-foreground`); default contrast |
| `'high'` | `shadow-md` / `shadow-lg` on key cards; accent colors; high-contrast CTA buttons |

---

## Dimension 7 — `ctaPolicy` (Call-to-Action Constraint)

| Value | Rule |
|---|---|
| `'minimal'` | Only contextual inline actions (row edit/delete); no standalone primary buttons |
| `'single-primary'` | Exactly one `severity="primary"` `<Button>` per logical section |
| `'dual-primary'` | Exactly two co-equal primary actions per section (e.g., "Save Draft" / "Publish") |

---

## Decision Workflow (Ordered)

When creating a new page, resolve all dimensions in this order before writing any markup:

1. **Identify** `intent` from the business requirement description
2. **Select** `archetype` — use the `intent` default mapping above unless overridden
3. **Set** `density` based on information load (table rows? reading? forms?)
4. **Set** `hierarchy` based on whether the user acts on or consumes the data
5. **Set** `emphasis` based on the visual weight this section should carry in the app
6. **Set** `ctaPolicy` based on the count of primary actions the page exposes

---

## Example Resolution

> Requirement: "User Management page — list all users, click row to open edit drawer."

```typescript
const pageState: UIDesignState = {
  intent:     'data-management',
  archetype:  'A4-table-drawer',  // table + row-click drawer
  density:    'compact',          // dense table: show maximum rows
  hierarchy:  'data-first',       // table is the primary surface
  emphasis:   'medium',           // standard admin page, no special urgency
  ctaPolicy:  'single-primary',   // one "New User" button in toolbar
}
```

This translates to:
- Skeleton: `A4-table-drawer` HTML structure (see above)
- Spacing: prefer `p-sm`, `gap-sm` for toolbar; `ProTable` fills remaining height
- Shadow: `shadow-sm` on card wrapper; standard `bg-card`
- Toolbar CTA: exactly one `<Button severity="primary" label="New User" />`

---

## Absolute Prohibitions

```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN: extending archetype enum
type ExtendedArchetype = UIDesignState['archetype'] | 'A6-my-custom-layout'

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: adding new intent without architect approval
// intent: 'reporting'  ← does not exist in UIDesignState

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: mapping density to SizeMode — they are DIFFERENT systems
if (state.density === 'spacious') {
  useSizeStore().setSize('loose') // NEVER — density ≠ SizeMode
}

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: using UIDesignState as a Vue component prop type
// defineProps<{ design: UIDesignState }>()  ← it is a spec, not runtime data

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: mixing archetype skeletons on one page
// Do not combine A3 stats grid AND A4 table as co-equal siblings at the root level
```
